# 📊 Clustering Analysis (Unsupervised Learning)

## 🔍 Overview

This project applies clustering techniques to group similar data points based on patterns and relationships without predefined labels.

## 📊 Model Approach

* K-Means clustering used
* Optimal number of clusters determined using Elbow Method

## 📈 Key Findings

* Data grouped into ~3–5 meaningful clusters
* Each cluster represents a distinct segment based on features
* Clear separation observed between clusters

## 📊 Insights

* Identified natural groupings in data
* Useful for segmentation (customers/products)
* Helps in targeted strategy development

## 📉 Observations

* Some overlap between clusters indicates complexity in data
* Cluster quality depends on feature scaling

## 💡 Applications

* Customer segmentation
* Market analysis
* Behavioral grouping

## 📌 Conclusion

Clustering successfully identified patterns in data and provided meaningful segmentation insights.
